  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Thou, who at Thy first Eucharist didst pray That all Thy Church might be forever one, Grant us at ev&#39;ry Eucharist to say With longing heart and soul, &quot;Thy will be done.&quot; O may we all one bread, one body be, Through this blest sacrament of uni- ty.",
    "v2": "For all Thy Church, O Lord, we intercede; Make Thou our sad divisions soon to cease; Draw us the nearer each to each, we plead, By drawing all to Thee, O Prince of Peace; Thus may we all one bread, one body be, Through this blest sacrament of uni- ty.",
    "v3": "We pray Thee too for wand&#39;rers from Thy fold; O bring them back, good Shepherd of the sheep, Back to the faith which saints believed of old, Back to the Church which still that faith doth keep; Soon may we all one bread, one body be, Through this blest sacrament of uni- ty.",
    "v4": "So, Lord, at length when sacraments shall cease, May we be one with all Thy Church above, One with Thy saints in one unbroken peace, One with Thy saints in one unbounded love; More blessèd still, in peace and love to be One with the Trini- ty in uni- ty."
  },
